rlGreenEth.name: rlGreenEth

revisions.description: Add Green Ethernet Energy Detect and Short Reach support per port and per system rlGreenEthernet

rlGreenEth.description: The private MIB module definition for Green Ethernet Energy Detect feature.

rlGreenEthEnergyDetectEnable.name: rlGreenEthEnergyDetectEnable
rlGreenEthEnergyDetectEnable.description: This scalar defines Green Ethernet Enrgy-Detect Globaly

rlGreenEthShortReachEnable.name: rlGreenEthShortReachEnable
rlGreenEthShortReachEnable.description: This scalar defines Green Ethernet Short-Reach Globaly

rlGreenEthCurrentEnergyConsumption.name: rlGreenEthCurrentEnergyConsumption
rlGreenEthCurrentEnergyConsumption.description: This scalar define Green Ethernet all modes current Energy consumption per system in mWatt in order to calculate current energy consumption in percent proportional to Consumption without Green Ethernet feature please use the following formula: (rlGreenEthCurrentEnergyConsumption/rlGreenEthCurrentMaxEnergyConsumption)*100

rlGreenEthCurrentMaxEnergyConsumption.name: rlGreenEthCurrentMaxEnergyConsumption
rlGreenEthCurrentMaxEnergyConsumption.description: This scalar define Green Ethernet current maximum consumption Energy consumption per system in mWatt, as it was without Green Ethernet feature.

rlGreenEthCumulativePowerSaveMeter.name: rlGreenEthCumulativePowerSaveMeter
rlGreenEthCumulativePowerSaveMeter.description: This scalar define Green Ethernet cumulative power save per system in Watt*Hour

rlGreenEthShortReachThreshold.name: rlGreenEthShortReachThreshold
rlGreenEthShortReachThreshold.description: The usage threshold expressed in meter for determinate the cable length for Short-Reach

rlGreenEthCumulativePowerSaveMeterReset.name: rlGreenEthCumulativePowerSaveMeterReset
rlGreenEthCumulativePowerSaveMeterReset.description: The rlGreenEthCumulativePowerSaveMeterReset indicates that rlGreenEthCumulativePowerSaveMeter should be set to ziro. This object behaviors as write-only than reading this object will always return 'false'.

RlGreenSavingType.name: RlGreenSavingType
RlGreenSavingType.description: Green saving types: energyDetect(1) uses energy detect shortReach(2) uses Short Reach

NonOperReasonType.name: NonOperReasonType
NonOperReasonType.description: Reason why Green Ethernet is not activated saving on a port NP(1) Port is not present - Applicable in ED & SR LT(2) Link Type is not supported(fiber, auto media setect) - Applicable in ED & SR LU(3) Port link is up - Applicable only in ED LS(4) Link speed is not supported (100M,10M,10G) - Applicable only in SR LL(5) Link length received from VCT test exceed threshold - Applicable only in SR ER(6) Errors detected on line and port revered back to Long Reach(only in enhanced mode) - Applicable only in SR LD(7) Port link is Down - Applicable only in SR unknown(8) In case that green Active or disable on port

rlGreenEthPortTable.name: rlGreenEthPortTable
rlGreenEthPortTable.description: A table of green state of ports

rlGreenEthPortEntry.name: rlGreenEthPortEntry
rlGreenEthPortEntry.description: An entry of green state of port

rlGreenEthPortNonOperReason.name: rlGreenEthPortNonOperReason
rlGreenEthPortNonOperReason.description: Reason why saving mode is not activated

rlGreenEthForceShortReachIfIndexList.name: rlGreenEthForceShortReachIfIndexList
rlGreenEthForceShortReachIfIndexList.description: The ports that forced enable the Green Ethernet Short Reach configuration not considering VCT results.
